Catherine Zeta-Jones, 52, looked the epitome of chic as the age-defying beauty donned a black ensemble two decades ago. The mum-of-two was joined by her husband Michael Douglas, 77, in Monte Carlo for the Laureus World Sports Awards Charity Gala. But the Darling Buds of May star almost suffered a dress malfunction as she attempted to get out of the car. The daring dress featured a plunging neckline with a thigh-high split as the beauty flashed her toned legs.